{[show NESW]
[ROLE leader][STAGE pre-lead] Lead the \HK, your singleton heart's natural companion is gone — the bare king is a normal aggressive start against the spade game.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE auction-end] Welcome to this shelf's final exam: six hands, and nobody will tell you which tool fits until you have played it. Board one: 4\S needing ten tricks. Trumps are strong, the diamonds look generous — but the defense has a trump trick's worth of mischief and two aces' worth of tricks coming. When your sure tricks come up one short and no finesse is on offer, this shelf taught you where the extra trick comes from — find it.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-play] A simple squeeze, served without a label: two threats, one busy defender, and the last trump as the executioner. Notice you never had a finesse to take — the extra trick could only be MADE, by pressure. One board down; the tools rotate from here.}
