[ROLE leader][STAGE pre-lead] Lead the \CK, top of your \CK-Q sequence — the standard attack against 3NT.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE auction-end] Board three: 3NT needing nine. The spade suit — your K-T-6-2 opposite dummy's A-8-7 — is missing the queen and jack, and no simple line picks up four of them on one side. The exam's question is quieter than a finesse: how many spades does WEST have, and how will you find out? Every trick the defense cashes, every exit he chooses, every card he pitches is testimony. Collect it.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-play] The show-up squeeze: no menace, no drama, just arithmetic — his exit gave you the jack, the ten survived, his pitch confessed, and the ace asked the final question. The queen never had a chance to be finessed for; she was simply counted out of hiding. Halfway home.}
